      "overview": "<p>Turn a love of food into a profession in a program built around real kitchen work.</p><p>You&rsquo;ll learn knife skills, classical cooking techniques, baking, garde manger, global cuisines, nutrition, and food cost control&mdash;practicing daily in production kitchens and building the speed, consistency, and professionalism that restaurants, hotels, resorts, and caterers expect.</p>",
      "employmentOutlook": "<p>Trained cooks are in steady demand across full-service restaurants, hotels, resorts, clubs, catering, contract foodservice, and healthcare. Graduates start as prep cook, line cook, or station chef and can earn American Culinary Federation certification, advancing with experience to sous chef, pastry chef, executive chef, or foodservice manager.</p><p>(Please note: CPCC does not guarantee employment)</p>",
